lender.name: Rolf
lender.loan_because:
I always admired the concept of giving the tithe back to God as practiced by various Christians, however I always had a problem with the idea of handing it over to institutions focused on pleasing the audience or followers.
I don’t judge does that do give to the church, because is an act of faith in God and not the institution, however, I choose to give my money back to God thanking for the blessings received in a more pragmatic way, were it won’t be used by the institution as part of their marketing campaign or expansion strategy.
Listening to the teaching of an independent Pastor from Brazil called Caio Fabio, that the money should first help the people closer to us, and that we should always listen to our heart in Christ, I decided to put that money to use for the good of the poorest.
I also never believed that other faiths need converting through the brain washing campaigns so many times funded by the religious establishments, but the enlightment in Christ needs to be an interpersonal experience and never an imposition, and that should always be led by example and not words.
I think these are the principles that guide my decision.
Rolf Henrich
